target.query:
from(bucket: "${bucket}")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "events")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_value"] =~ /.* started/)
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: last, createEmpty: false)

from(bucket: "${bucket}")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "events")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_value"] =~ /.* ended/)
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: last, createEmpty: false)

description: JMeter performance testing live results dashboard, utilizing Flux queries (Influxdb 2.x)

targets.query:
from(bucket: "${bucket}")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop: v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._measurement == "${measurement_name}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r.application == "${application}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r._field == "avg")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r.testTitle == "${testTitle1}" or r.testTitle == "${testTitle2}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r.transaction =~ /^[A-Za-z]+$/ or r.transaction =~ /^[A-Za-z]+[A-Za-z]+$/)
  |> group(columns: ["testTitle", "transaction"])
  |> mean()
  |> group()
  |> pivot(rowKey: ["transaction"], columnKey: ["testTitle"], valueColumn: "_value")

list.definition:
from(bucket: "${bucket}")
  |> range(start: v.timeRangeStart, stop:v.timeRangeStop)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "${measurement_name}")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["application"] == "${application}")
  |> group()
  |> distinct(column: "transaction") 
  |> drop(columns: ["_start", "_stop"])
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_value"] != "internal")
